  "nerocq": "The nerocq is a monstrous hunting-beast of Leithicor, prized by the servants of the Guardian Bemoth as a mount and a hound of war.",
  "demon-noble": "Demon nobles are exceedingly mighty demons, perhaps supreme commanders or rulers of some lesser princedom or sphere of torment.",
  "demon-prince": "There are eight demon princes besides Zahmet himself, ruler of Inferno.",
  "echram-schroedel": "A war-demon out of the sixth circle of Inferno, the Circle of Wars, whose true name is Z'crohederc and who hates everything that Altor is.",
  "greater-demon": "The greater demons are those that have survived long enough to climb a fair way up the ranks of Inferno.",
  "urbaug-the-insane": "A guardian demon of the ninth circle, sent to Altor to set right the ruin he himself has caused.",
  "chaos-dragon": "Chaos dragons are the very opposite of gold dragons in their general bearing.",
  "dragon": "Of all the monsters in the world the dragon stands apart, and not for its size and fire alone.",
  "dragonsnake": "Dragonsnakes are only distant kin to the mightiest of all creatures, the dragons, and lack most of the special powers and traits that set true dragons apart.",
  "fire-dragon": "Fire-dragons are the commonest kind of dragon and most likely the ancestral stock from which all the other kinds descend.",
  "gold-dragon": "Gold dragons are the most magnificent and imposing of all dragons, and at the same time by far the rarest, for they live far longer than any other kind yet…",
  "ice-dragon": "Ice dragons make their homes in the coldest climates and are happiest amid cold and snow, though they fare perfectly well in any climate, for a dragon's…",
  "light-dragon": "Light dragons are close kin to fire-dragons, though much smaller and nowhere near as powerful.",
  "lindworm": "Lindworms are a kind of cross between dragons and dragonsnakes.",
  "sea-dragon": "Sea dragons differ greatly in form from the other dragons, but they share most of the fire-dragon's powers.",
  "sea-serpent": "Sea serpents are vast serpent-like monsters found in most seas and in some great lakes and rivers.",
  "djinn": "Djinn dwell on the elemental plane of air.",
  "earth-beetle": "Earth beetles dwell on the elemental plane of earth.",
