  "undin": "Elementals are incarnations of the elements, summoned from the elemental planes into our world by a magician's elemental magic.",
  "acid-lizard": "Acid lizards are large black predatory lizards that normally live on insects, rodents, fish and bats, but in larger company, more than five of them, will also…",
  "alfin": "The alfin, or elf-cat, is a small and uncanny feline that keeps the company of the elf-folk.",
  "ambiorm": "The ambiorm is a rightly feared creature: a great serpent that bears, where its tail ought to be, a second head.",
  "angyon": "The angyon is a large, two-legged beast long bred and broken to the saddle and the pack.",
  "arboreal-leech": "Tree-leeches live in the treetops of dark, damp deciduous forests.",
  "aries": "The aries is an amphibious predator with the power to turn its hind legs into a long fish-tail when it is in the water.",
  "basilisk": "The reptilian basilisk and its petrifying gaze are no matter for a novice adventurer, though a seasoned fighter usually has a fair chance against the vile…",
  "brook-bear": "The brook bear is a good-natured little creature, no taller than a metre when it rears up on its hind legs, and despite the name it puts one more in mind of a…",
  "chimera": "In one of the most turbulent of the Chaos realms, a bored Chaos lord created the chimeras.",
  "cockatrice": "The basilisk's larger cousin, the cockatrice is often called.",
  "death-owl": "It is said that the death owls' ancestral home lies in the deep forests of the north.",
  "demon-cat": "There are rumours of fearsome demon-cats, beasts that kill every intruder in their territory.",
  "drinnen": "The drinnen is a strange beast of the Aidne marshes, found nowhere else: a low, scaled hunter of the reeds and shallows.",
  "dwarf-horse": "The dwarf-horse is a small, hardy horse of the Montures, running wild on the pasture-isle of Jalujak.",
  "elefantine": "The elefantiner are tiny wild \"elephants\" of Magilre, scarcely a metre tall and famously ferocious for their size.",
  "elephant-bird": "The elephant bird is the largest bird that has ever lived, standing more than three and a half metres tall and weighing upward of six hundred kilos.",
  "eye-beast": "Eye-beasts are very dangerous predators that live in small packs of between four and eight.",
  "flying-lizard": "Flying lizards are large reptiles with short legs and an enormously broad wingspan.",
  "forgyor": "The forgyor is a predatory fish of the deep sea, and sailors who have met a hunting flock of them rarely care to speak of it afterwards.",
  "gargoyle": "Some believe gargoyles are stone statues perched on temples and old castles, brought to life by mad magicians.",
  "ghertum": "A ghertûm is no creature in the ordinary sense, but rather a being made up of millions of tiny silver-grey insects that hold together in so dense a swarm that…",
  "giant-amoeba": "A giant amoeba is a great, foul-smelling lump of slime whose chief occupation is to find organic matter it can absorb.",
  "giant-octopus": "A monstrous octopus of the coastal depths and the open sea, the common kind some six metres across the reach of its arms, though the oldest grow far larger.",
  "giant-spider": "Giant spiders are fearsome, intelligent predators that live either in hidden underground caves or in the canopy of some unusually dark and unpleasant forest.",
  "giant-turtle": "The giant turtle is a vast and ancient sea-turtle, its shell broad enough that sailors have been known to take a sleeping one for a low island and land upon…",
  "gorgon": "It is said that only three gorgons exist.",
  "grey-mareskunk": "The grey mareskunk is a marsh creature unique in that its only weapon is wholly of the mind: it learns the thoughts of others and casts them back at its victim.",
  "griffin": "Griffins are aggressive and dangerous predators.",
  "harebir": "The harebir is a huge, frog-like beast of the deep sea, so rarely seen that most who live by the coast never lay eyes on one in a lifetime.",
  "harpy": "Harpies so hate their own existence that they find no pleasure in life but to spread as much misery around them as they can.",
  "high-warden-tiger": "The high warden tiger belongs by origin to the deep jungles of the far east.",
  "hippocampus": "The hippocampus is a sea-beast with the foreparts of a horse and, in place of hind legs, the long coiling tail of a great fish.",
